      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/belford_new_jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The area that became Belford was part of Middletown Township, one of New Jersey’s earliest colonial seats founded in 1664 under the Monmouth Patent.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        1,
        2
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1",
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/belford_new_jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Belford sits on a low‑lying coastal plain, only about 10 feet above sea level, making it vulnerable to tidal surges from Sandy Hook Bay.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        23
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/belford_new_jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Ware Creek and its tidal marsh lie to the east of Belford, adding to the area’s natural waterfront character.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        28
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
